PUH-BrianMartell this directly strengthens the quantitative side of PUH by giving a concrete, testable prediction for the growth rate observable fσ₈(z). The S₈ tension is closely related to deviations in structure growth history, and a redshift-dependent suppression in fσ₈(z) at low-to-intermediate redshifts (z ≲ 1) is exactly what many surveys (including combined DES/DESI constraints) hint at relative to pure CMB extrapolation. I’ve added a new subsection with a simple but physically motivated phenomenological equation for the modified linear growth in PUH. The idea is that photonic energy injection from Planck-star jets becomes non-negligible only at late times (a ≳ 0.5–0.6, roughly z ≲ 1), producing an effective negative-pressure-like feedback that suppresses the growth rate of perturbations without altering the background expansion (keeping w ≈ −1).
